Navigate to the EC2 Dashboard.
In navigation panel locate Security group in Network & Secuirty Tab
Initiate Creation: Click the "Create security group" button.
Config basic setting by providing NAME of security group and description of security group
Select the VPC where you want to create this security group.
Under the "Inbound rules" section, click "Add rule."
Type (e.g., SSH, HTTP, HTTPS, Custom TCP Rule)(e.g., My IP, Anywhere IIPV4, or another Security Group ID) for incoming traffic that should be allowed.
Review and Create: Review your configured rules and settings, then click "Create security group." 
